article.headline: Bears breaks game open in second half
article.story:
SPRINGFIELD, Mo. (AP) -- Tamarr Maclin scored 20 points to lead
Southwest Missouri State to a 105-82 win over Rice on Wednesday in
the opening round of the NIT.

	   Michael Harris led Rice (19-12) with 24 points. Morris Almond
scored 14 and Brock Gillespie added 10.

	   Rice coach Willis Wilson was ejected 33 seconds into the second
half after receiving two technicals from referee Bryan Kersey.
Wilson got the first for being outside the coach's box and was
ejected when he came on the court to confront Kersey.

	   Wilson had been complaining to officials in the first half about
some of the calls against his team.

	   Southwest Missouri State went on a 21-13 after Wilson was
ejected to go up 61-42 with 14:37 left.

	   The Bears (19-12), playing their first postseason tournament in
five years, will play Davidson on Saturday night in Springfield.

	   Neither team led by more than three in the first half until
Southwest Missouri broke away from Rice on 11-4 run to take a 28-20
lead with 6:15 left and then closed with another 12-9 run to lead
40-29 at halftime despite 12 points from Harris.

	   Blake Ahearn scored 15 for the Bears, Tyler Chaney had 13 and
Kellen Easley 12.
